1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the per-user multiplexing gain in a wireless network, which is a key concept in information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on the effect of conferencing rounds on the capacity of a large interference network, which is a topic related to networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper deals with a network of transmitters and receivers, which can be considered a social network. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper mentions the capacity of the transmitter- and receiver-conferencing links, which can be related to multimedia transmission. 
5. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper presents upper and lower bounds on the per-user MG, which can be considered a computational problem.
